8\log_n u \cdot \log_m v - 7\log_n u-6\log_m v - 2013 &= 0\\
8uv - 7u - 6v - 2013 &= 0 & \text{(since } \log_n u = \dfrac{1}{\log_u n} \text{, and }\log_m v = \dfrac{1}{\log_v m} \text{)}\\
0 &= -7u - 6v + 2013 + 8uv\\
0 &= 8u^2 + (uv-7)u + (4v-2013) \qquad \text{(quadratic equation in } u\text{)}
\end{align*}The product of the roots of this equation is $\dfrac{4v-2013}{8}\text{. }
It's given that the product is a positive integer; we also have $u,v>0$. It's easy to realize that the minimum integer answer is achieved by letting $v = 504$ which gives the product $mn = 441 \Longrightarrow \boxed{0+504=......}$</answer>

